Create a programm that
- opens specified files with O_NONBLOCK
- polls them until reading is avaliable
- reads from fds and prints into stdout


Example:
./a.out file1 file2 file3


where file1, file2, file3 is fifo (mkfifo)

___________________________
RUN
gcc task.c -o run
mkfifo file1
mkfifo file2
mkfifo file3
terminal1           terminal2
./run               echo "Hello" > file1
                    echo "World" > file2
                    echo "What do I do in my life?" > file3
